pr_title: [NEW] REST function to fetch list of members of a group
pr_body:
members list is used to show members while adding @ mentioning
Resolve #64
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 956738540, 'comment_body': '`general` is not a group but channel. The difference is subtle, both are considered "rooms" but public ones are channels and private ones are groups. In this particular case `groups.*` endpoints do not check any public rooms, i.e. channels, which general is. ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 28, 14, 38, 4, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'debdutdeb', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 956739847, 'comment_body': 'a visual example
```sh
$ culr https://open.rocket.chat/api/v1/groups.members\?roomId\=GENERAL
{"success":false,"error":"The required \"roomId\" or \"roomName\" param provided does not match any group [error-room-not-found]","errorType":"error-room-not-found"}%
$ culr https://open.rocket.chat/api/v1/channels.members\?roomId\=GENERAL -s | jq .success
true
```', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 28, 14, 46, 55, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'debdutdeb', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 958062139, 'comment_body': 'you are right. General is a channel and using it to get members of a group will eventually fail. To add test for it I can make a private group run tests on it and then delete it. As I see function to create private group exists in realtime API so I think I can use it.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 30, 6, 38, 45, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'srrathi', 'type': 'User'}]
